## Read Before Use

This web proxy is designed to work with Vercel and static serverless sites. It forwards requests to the target origin and serves the response back to the client.

To use this proxy, you will need to:

1. Deploy the proxy to a serverless platform, such as Vercel or Netlify.
2. Configure the proxy to forward requests to your target origin.
3. Update your DNS records to point to the proxy's URL.

## Features

* Supports HTTP and HTTPS requests
* Forwards headers and cookies
* Caches responses
* Compresses responses

## Limitations

* Does not support websockets
* Does not support streaming requests

## Troubleshooting

If you are experiencing problems with the proxy, please check the following:

* Ensure that the proxy is deployed to a serverless platform.
* Ensure that the proxy is configured to forward requests to your target origin.
* Ensure that your DNS records are pointing to the proxy's URL.
* Check the proxy's logs for any errors.

## Contributing

Contributions are welcome! Please read the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/web-proxy/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md) before submitting a pull request.
